      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BONNIE BOUQUET (6) has switched from a Victorian stable to Stuart Kendrick on a 34-day turnaround. She was beaten 1.5L over 1412m at Echuca when last seen, and following sharp jumpouts, she'd been well supported over 1170m at Wangaratta on debut. Has a handy 3kg claim, and this is winnable if she's presented on song. BOWDENE (3) was on speed and just missed here on debut. Resumes owning two sharp 1000m trials at the track and has plenty of scope for improvement. Draws out but has plenty of early speed. JOLLY JAPES debuts for the McCall yard and has been well educated. She can be very competitive on what we've seen. I WANT IT ALL (7) (8) is a local on debut and just missed in a recent 1000m trial here. Maps well, and she's also worth a betting watch.",
